This is a standard failure and is due to an fvwm mouse binding 
conflicting with one built into the process.  It is usually a button in 
the window.  I use 

Mouse 1         W       M       RaiseLower

rather than the system.fvwm(2)rc file.  If this is not in the FAQ, then it 
should be.  I had to find it myself, and it is asked several times a year 
on the list.

